1
00:01:31,520 --> 00:01:35,070
[NORTHWARD]

2
00:01:35,110 --> 00:01:36,860
[Episode 2]

3
00:01:57,550 --> 00:01:58,390
What's wrong?

4
00:01:58,390 --> 00:02:01,120
You're so quiet this morning, looking troubled.

5
00:02:01,390 --> 00:02:03,610
It's about the new ship.

6
00:02:03,640 --> 00:02:05,440
He believes we can make a profit.

7
00:02:05,660 --> 00:02:07,030
What if we can't?

8
00:02:07,590 --> 00:02:09,949
But it's been profitable, hasn't it?

9
00:02:10,229 --> 00:02:11,070
On this canal,

10
00:02:11,070 --> 00:02:12,580
Boss Xie is an expert.

11
00:02:12,610 --> 00:02:13,830
He can't be wrong.

12
00:02:13,830 --> 00:02:15,030
Don't think too much.

13
00:02:15,440 --> 00:02:16,800
Have you done the math?

14
00:02:16,850 --> 00:02:20,570
[Breakfast]

15
00:02:17,100 --> 00:02:18,440
Yes.

16
00:02:18,710 --> 00:02:21,110
It's profitable if we can get many clients.

17
00:02:21,470 --> 00:02:23,750
But it's just a small business.

18
00:02:24,160 --> 00:02:25,840
I don't dare take risks.

19
00:02:25,890 --> 00:02:26,810
Besides,

20
00:02:26,829 --> 00:02:29,310
it's just Xie and Lao'er now.

21
00:02:29,880 --> 00:02:31,110
They can handle

22
00:02:31,150 --> 00:02:32,070
a 500-ton ship.

23
00:02:32,070 --> 00:02:33,220
But if they trade up,

24
00:02:33,270 --> 00:02:34,200
I'm afraid

25
00:02:34,470 --> 00:02:35,680
they'll have to hire another person.

26
00:02:35,680 --> 00:02:37,590
The cost

27
00:02:37,590 --> 00:02:39,230
will definitely increase a lot.

28
00:02:39,230 --> 00:02:40,440
Yeah.

29
00:02:40,590 --> 00:02:41,430
How much will that cost?

30
00:02:41,430 --> 00:02:42,390
Coming.

31
00:02:42,560 --> 00:02:43,579
I gotta go.

32
00:02:44,100 --> 00:02:45,510
Coming. Coming.

33
00:02:48,150 --> 00:02:49,310
Stir before eating.

34
00:02:53,340 --> 00:02:55,070
Xie Wanghe, why are you so late?

35
00:02:55,140 --> 00:02:57,070
I forgot to set an alarm last night.

36
00:02:57,070 --> 00:02:57,710
You…

37
00:02:58,510 --> 00:02:59,590
This isn't over!

38
00:02:59,590 --> 00:03:01,650
I'll teach you a lesson after school!

39
00:03:01,670 --> 00:03:03,670
Watch your step!

40
00:03:07,950 --> 00:03:09,870
Wait, wait, wait!

41
00:03:09,870 --> 00:03:10,430
You brat.

42
00:03:10,430 --> 00:03:11,420
You're late!

43
00:03:18,170 --> 00:03:19,590
Class, take out your textbook

44
00:03:19,590 --> 00:03:21,150
and turn to page 54.

45
00:03:21,270 --> 00:03:22,060
May I come in?

46
00:03:22,230 --> 00:03:23,660
Why are you late again?

47
00:03:23,760 --> 00:03:24,950
You don't pay attention in class

48
00:03:24,950 --> 00:03:26,610
and are always late to school.

49
00:03:26,910 --> 00:03:29,020
If this goes on, I'll call your father.

50
00:03:29,020 --> 00:03:30,270
I won't be late again.

51
00:03:30,290 --> 00:03:31,090
Come in.

52
00:03:32,030 --> 00:03:33,660
Come on. Let's continue.

53
00:03:37,870 --> 00:03:38,860
Fenghua!

54
00:03:39,620 --> 00:03:40,530
Madam,

55
00:03:40,560 --> 00:03:41,670
Xie Wanghe is threatening me!

56
00:03:41,670 --> 00:03:43,150
No. She tripped me first!

57
00:03:43,070 --> 00:03:44,900
[Mountain Trip]

58
00:03:43,150 --> 00:03:43,790
We're in class!

59
00:03:43,790 --> 00:03:45,110
Be quiet! Sit down.

60
00:03:46,220 --> 00:03:48,150
Today, we're going to learn a poem called

61
00:03:48,150 --> 00:03:49,230
"Mountain Trip."

62
00:03:49,230 --> 00:03:50,550
Can anyone tell me

63
00:03:50,590 --> 00:03:52,790
what season this poem is about?

64
00:03:53,310 --> 00:03:54,190
Okay, Chen Rui.

65
00:03:54,710 --> 00:03:55,790
Autumn.

66
00:03:55,790 --> 00:03:56,710
Great. Autumn.

67
00:03:56,750 --> 00:03:57,350
Sit down.

68
00:03:57,880 --> 00:04:00,360
Let's read this poem together, shall we?

69
00:04:00,650 --> 00:04:03,710
"Walking up the rocky path in the cold mountain."

70
00:04:03,780 --> 00:04:08,300
"Walking up the rocky path in the cold mountain."

71
00:04:08,330 --> 00:04:11,160
"Amid rising white clouds, a village was seen."

72
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:15,510
"Amid rising white clouds, a village was seen."

73
00:04:15,630 --> 00:04:18,839
"I stopped the coach, drawn by the maple woods at dusk."

74
00:04:18,860 --> 00:04:23,290
-"I stopped the coach, drawn by the maple woods at dusk."
-Director.

75
00:04:23,870 --> 00:04:26,730
[Mountain Trip]

76
00:04:25,070 --> 00:04:26,830
She just transferred

77
00:04:26,830 --> 00:04:28,430
from another school.

78
00:04:29,710 --> 00:04:31,030
She lives in our neighborhood.

79
00:04:31,030 --> 00:04:31,960
She's so pretty.

80
00:04:32,020 --> 00:04:33,700
Is she going to study with us?

81
00:04:35,950 --> 00:04:37,310
What's your name?

82
00:04:37,350 --> 00:04:38,230
Ma Siyi.

83
00:04:38,550 --> 00:04:40,180
What? Louder!

84
00:04:40,230 --> 00:04:41,159
I can't hear you.

85
00:04:41,270 --> 00:04:42,070
She said Ma Siyi!

86
00:04:42,070 --> 00:04:42,950
Are you deaf?

87
00:04:42,950 --> 00:04:44,110
I'll get you for this.

88
00:04:44,110 --> 00:04:46,030
There's an empty seat over there.

89
00:04:46,070 --> 00:04:46,830
Go.

90
00:04:46,830 --> 00:04:47,909
Siyi, sit here.

91
00:04:49,870 --> 00:04:50,770
Siyi.

92
00:04:51,870 --> 00:04:54,180
Okay. Let's finish reading this poem.

93
00:04:54,270 --> 00:04:57,510
"Frosty leaves were redder than flowers in February."

94
00:04:57,570 --> 00:05:01,140
"Frosty leaves were redder than flowers in February."

95
00:05:01,160 --> 00:05:01,750
Siyi.

96
00:05:01,790 --> 00:05:04,070
"Frosty leaves were redder than flowers in February." Great.

97
00:05:04,070 --> 00:05:05,560
Frosty leaves are…

98
00:05:05,580 --> 00:05:06,580
Siyi.

99
00:05:06,610 --> 00:05:09,310
What kind of leaves are they?

100
00:05:09,420 --> 00:05:12,670
Maple leaves. Yes. Maple leaves.

101
00:05:12,700 --> 00:05:14,410
What color are maple leaves?

102
00:05:14,490 --> 00:05:15,070
Red.

103
00:05:15,070 --> 00:05:15,990
Madam,

104
00:05:15,990 --> 00:05:17,670
Xie Wanghe is disrupting the class order!

105
00:05:17,670 --> 00:05:19,070
What do you want, Xia Fenghua?

106
00:05:19,070 --> 00:05:20,390
Xie Wanghe!

107
00:05:20,410 --> 00:05:21,520
Xie Wanghe!

108
00:05:22,220 --> 00:05:23,070
Get out!

109
00:05:23,070 --> 00:05:25,390
Xia Fenghua pushed me first.

110
00:05:25,390 --> 00:05:26,350
Get out!

111
00:05:30,790 --> 00:05:32,070
Xia Fenghua!

112
00:05:32,070 --> 00:05:33,150
You go out too!

113
00:05:33,190 --> 00:05:35,250
Stand on either side of the corridor.

114
00:05:37,840 --> 00:05:39,340
Come on, let's continue.

115
00:05:39,590 --> 00:05:41,380
They're redder

116
00:05:41,380 --> 00:05:43,600
than flowers in February.

117
00:05:43,750 --> 00:05:47,350
The first line: "Walking up the rocky path in the cold mountain."

118
00:05:47,500 --> 00:05:50,790
Going into the mountain in late autumn.

119
00:05:50,830 --> 00:05:52,330
The mountain road…

120
00:05:52,550 --> 00:06:02,140
[Flower Street Dock]

121
00:05:52,600 --> 00:05:53,320
Granny.

122
00:05:54,550 --> 00:05:56,070
Siyi will stay?

123
00:05:58,390 --> 00:06:00,590
I got her into the local school.

124
00:06:00,630 --> 00:06:02,390
She'll stay here.

125
00:06:02,720 --> 00:06:04,480
What is her mother thinking?

126
00:06:04,520 --> 00:06:05,870
Is she really her mother?

127
00:06:05,870 --> 00:06:06,740
If someone

128
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:08,480
tried to steal Fenghua,

129
00:06:08,510 --> 00:06:09,970
I'd stop them at all costs!

130
00:06:10,100 --> 00:06:10,950
Well,

131
00:06:10,950 --> 00:06:12,550
she remarried

132
00:06:12,550 --> 00:06:13,670
and had another child.

133
00:06:13,670 --> 00:06:16,390
She can't raise two kids at the same time.

134
00:06:16,410 --> 00:06:17,620
It's not easy for her.

135
00:06:17,640 --> 00:06:18,990
Then she shouldn't have had another kid.

136
00:06:18,990 --> 00:06:19,990
How could a mother

137
00:06:20,020 --> 00:06:21,280
abandon her own child?

138
00:06:21,350 --> 00:06:22,860
Don't be so harsh.

139
00:06:22,900 --> 00:06:24,570
She had the right to remarry.

140
00:06:24,620 --> 00:06:25,280
Yes.

141
00:06:25,320 --> 00:06:26,030
Yuling.

142
00:06:26,190 --> 00:06:28,300
What would you do if you were her?

143
00:06:29,210 --> 00:06:30,710
Isn't it obvious?

144
00:06:30,740 --> 00:06:32,320
Children are the most important.

145
00:06:32,320 --> 00:06:33,480
If I remarry,

146
00:06:33,510 --> 00:06:34,300
I must get

147
00:06:34,330 --> 00:06:35,550
Fenghua's permission first,

148
00:06:35,550 --> 00:06:36,120
right?

149
00:06:36,140 --> 00:06:38,390
Mom, who's remarrying?

150
00:06:38,430 --> 00:06:39,230
What did Dad do?

151
00:06:39,230 --> 00:06:41,070
My god.

152
00:06:41,110 --> 00:06:41,670
The adults are talking.

153
00:06:41,670 --> 00:06:42,630
Don't interrupt!

154
00:06:42,630 --> 00:06:43,390
Go away!

155
00:06:43,390 --> 00:06:44,990
Go home and do your homework.

156
00:06:46,430 --> 00:06:49,380
How was your first day at school?

157
00:06:49,380 --> 00:06:50,550
Not bad.

158
00:06:52,110 --> 00:06:53,550
Good.

159
00:06:54,460 --> 00:06:55,540
Are you hungry?

160
00:06:55,950 --> 00:06:56,659
Let me get you a…

161
00:06:56,659 --> 00:06:57,409
Well…

162
00:06:57,450 --> 00:06:58,480
I have sesame balls here.

163
00:06:57,500 --> 00:06:59,080
[By the Canal]

164
00:06:58,490 --> 00:06:59,500
Siyi, here.

165
00:07:00,220 --> 00:07:01,500
Have a sesame ball.

166
00:07:01,520 --> 00:07:02,470
Try it.

167
00:07:04,520 --> 00:07:05,980
Is it good?

168
00:07:08,390 --> 00:07:09,720
It's delicious, right?

169
00:07:19,300 --> 00:07:19,910
Here.

170
00:07:21,060 --> 00:07:23,390
Mom, the braised pork you made is amazing.

171
00:07:23,790 --> 00:07:25,040
Don't just eat meat.

172
00:07:25,070 --> 00:07:25,870
Eating too much meat

173
00:07:25,870 --> 00:07:26,870
will make you fat.

174
00:07:26,870 --> 00:07:28,730
Then Wanghe won't marry you after he grows up.

175
00:07:28,730 --> 00:07:30,160
He wouldn't dare.

176
00:07:30,180 --> 00:07:31,310
Why not?

177
00:07:31,620 --> 00:07:32,550
I just know it.

178
00:07:34,520 --> 00:07:35,720
Don't burn yourself.

179
00:07:37,159 --> 00:07:37,930
Delicious.

180
00:07:38,260 --> 00:07:39,150
Go eat inside.

181
00:07:41,850 --> 00:07:42,909
Wanghe.

182
00:07:43,570 --> 00:07:45,740
Come. Bring the dishes over.

183
00:07:45,770 --> 00:07:46,659
Coming.

184
00:07:49,190 --> 00:07:50,180
Okay.

185
00:08:00,750 --> 00:08:01,550
Siyi.

186
00:08:01,580 --> 00:08:03,690
Here, have another bun.

187
00:08:03,720 --> 00:08:04,450
Here.

188
00:08:04,660 --> 00:08:05,860
I'm full.

189
00:08:09,390 --> 00:08:09,950
Siyi.

190
00:08:09,950 --> 00:08:11,550
Are you feeling unwell?

191
00:08:11,550 --> 00:08:12,680
Tell me.

192
00:08:13,230 --> 00:08:14,030
No.

193
00:08:16,040 --> 00:08:17,310
Then have another bun.

194
00:08:17,310 --> 00:08:19,110
You're growing.

195
00:08:19,110 --> 00:08:21,950
Grandma, I really can't eat anymore.

196
00:08:22,750 --> 00:08:24,270
Enjoy your dinner.

197
00:08:24,550 --> 00:08:27,330
I'll wash the dishes after I finish my homework.

198
00:09:37,360 --> 00:09:38,950
Are you almost done?

199
00:09:38,950 --> 00:09:39,990
One pot left.

200
00:09:39,990 --> 00:09:41,420
Almost done?

201
00:09:42,930 --> 00:09:44,860
It's really not easy work.

202
00:09:44,860 --> 00:09:47,500
You get up two hours earlier than us every day.

203
00:09:47,500 --> 00:09:48,690
Yeah.

204
00:09:50,310 --> 00:09:52,110
Why don't you do something else?

205
00:09:53,740 --> 00:09:55,480
What else can I do?

206
00:09:55,990 --> 00:09:58,060
When will they come back today?

207
00:09:58,230 --> 00:09:59,360
No idea.

208
00:09:59,410 --> 00:10:00,630
Those men

209
00:10:00,630 --> 00:10:02,190
forget their homes when they're at sea.

210
00:10:02,190 --> 00:10:03,190
They wish they could never come back.

211
00:10:03,190 --> 00:10:03,670
Morning.

212
00:10:03,670 --> 00:10:04,870
Granny Ma, let me help you.

213
00:10:04,870 --> 00:10:05,540
No need.

214
00:10:05,540 --> 00:10:06,310
No need.

215
00:10:07,110 --> 00:10:08,710
Go on with your work.

216
00:10:09,070 --> 00:10:10,500
Did you use the herbal plaster I gave you yesterday?

217
00:10:10,500 --> 00:10:11,670
Yes.

218
00:10:11,670 --> 00:10:12,670
Granny Ma.

219
00:10:12,670 --> 00:10:14,750
Morning.

220
00:10:14,840 --> 00:10:16,250
Everything's set?

221
00:10:16,570 --> 00:10:17,700
Be careful.

222
00:10:18,310 --> 00:10:18,860
Okay.

223
00:10:18,860 --> 00:10:19,870
Careful.

224
00:10:21,330 --> 00:10:22,270
Let me help you.

225
00:10:22,270 --> 00:10:23,670
I'm good.

226
00:10:23,720 --> 00:10:24,600
Let me help you.

227
00:10:24,600 --> 00:10:25,390
I got it.

228
00:10:25,660 --> 00:10:27,030
Yan, pick that up for me.

229
00:10:27,030 --> 00:10:27,510
Okay.

230
00:10:27,510 --> 00:10:28,190
Be careful.

231
00:10:28,230 --> 00:10:29,390
Take it down.

232
00:10:42,030 --> 00:10:43,760
Thank you. Please come again.

233
00:10:43,830 --> 00:10:44,840
Fresh-made mung bean cakes!

234
00:10:44,840 --> 00:10:46,170
Come take a look!

235
00:10:46,230 --> 00:10:46,990
Wanghe.

236
00:10:46,280 --> 00:10:51,680
[Flower Street Dock]

237
00:10:47,270 --> 00:10:49,260
Your dad is a real man.

238
00:10:50,350 --> 00:10:51,350
What do you mean?

239
00:10:52,230 --> 00:10:53,730
Come on. Eat your fill.

240
00:10:53,730 --> 00:10:55,710
Last night, when I was sleeping,

241
00:10:56,050 --> 00:10:58,230
I heard your dad snoring.

242
00:10:58,990 --> 00:11:01,480
He snored even louder than Li Yuanba.

243
00:11:01,590 --> 00:11:02,510
Hurry up.

244
00:11:02,510 --> 00:11:03,750
Finish it and go to school.

245
00:11:03,750 --> 00:11:04,590
If you're late again,

246
00:11:04,590 --> 00:11:05,990
you're cooked.

247
00:11:05,990 --> 00:11:07,510
Mom, it's Saturday.

248
00:11:10,020 --> 00:11:11,250
Still, eat quickly.

249
00:11:11,360 --> 00:11:12,500
Then go do your thing.

250
00:11:12,500 --> 00:11:14,110
Don't sit at the table for long.

251
00:11:14,110 --> 00:11:14,750
Mom.

252
00:11:16,370 --> 00:11:17,660
Give me five yuan.

253
00:11:18,860 --> 00:11:20,010
Take it yourself.

254
00:11:20,160 --> 00:11:20,960
Here.

255
00:11:23,370 --> 00:11:24,500
Only five yuan.

256
00:11:25,090 --> 00:11:26,030
Thank you, Mom.

257
00:11:26,220 --> 00:11:27,710
Guys, let's go.

258
00:11:29,870 --> 00:11:30,960
Your breakfast!

259
00:11:31,140 --> 00:11:32,740
You haven't finished it yet!

260
00:11:33,710 --> 00:11:36,110
Those kids ran off as soon as they were full.

261
00:11:36,370 --> 00:11:37,970
He took the money and ran off.

262
00:11:38,840 --> 00:11:40,250
I want one!

263
00:11:40,930 --> 00:11:42,030
I want one!

264
00:11:42,690 --> 00:11:43,190
I want one!

265
00:11:43,190 --> 00:11:44,590
Why are you following us?

266
00:11:45,500 --> 00:11:46,840
Aren't you afraid of having a toothache

267
00:11:46,840 --> 00:11:47,910
after eating it all by yourself?

268
00:11:47,910 --> 00:11:50,910
Even if I lose all my teeth, it's none of your business.

269
00:11:53,850 --> 00:11:55,520
Stop following me.

270
00:12:00,670 --> 00:12:01,830
You want a bite?

271
00:12:04,750 --> 00:12:07,190
Five yuan per bite. You can pay in installments.

272
00:12:07,190 --> 00:12:09,190
Are you looking for a beating again?

273
00:12:29,820 --> 00:12:30,580
Hello?

274
00:12:30,980 --> 00:12:31,740
Mom.

275
00:12:32,300 --> 00:12:33,830
I dreamed of you last night.

276
00:12:34,430 --> 00:12:35,770
Grandma said…

277
00:12:36,390 --> 00:12:37,630
Grandma said…

278
00:12:40,540 --> 00:12:41,470
Siyi,

279
00:12:41,500 --> 00:12:43,090
just tell me what it is.

280
00:12:43,320 --> 00:12:44,560
Why are you crying?

281
00:12:44,670 --> 00:12:45,950
You're a big girl now.

282
00:12:46,470 --> 00:12:49,150
Mom, how long do I have to stay at Grandma's?

283
00:12:49,150 --> 00:12:50,890
When will you take me back?

284
00:12:51,100 --> 00:12:53,270
I can look after my brother for you.

285
00:12:53,300 --> 00:12:55,030
It won't affect my schoolwork.

286
00:12:55,150 --> 00:12:56,910
I can also do the laundry and cook.

287
00:12:55,420 --> 00:12:58,720
♫Far away, so far away♫

288
00:12:56,910 --> 00:12:58,630
I can do most of the housework.

289
00:12:59,540 --> 00:13:03,070
♫The hometown I can never return to♫

290
00:12:59,990 --> 00:13:01,820
Can't you be more considerate?

291
00:13:02,860 --> 00:13:04,310
Your grandma is getting on in years

292
00:13:04,140 --> 00:13:06,750
♫Sitting quietly in the city♫

