What a coincidence.

592
00:25:19,140 --> 00:25:20,540
Chen Bo told me

593
00:25:20,570 --> 00:25:22,350
that you're writing "The Story of the Canal."

594
00:25:22,350 --> 00:25:23,110
Yes.

595
00:25:23,400 --> 00:25:25,190
Don't forget to highlight

596
00:25:25,190 --> 00:25:26,950
Shuipu District and Flower Street.

597
00:25:26,950 --> 00:25:28,560
Of course.

598
00:25:28,630 --> 00:25:29,740
If that's the case,

599
00:25:29,740 --> 00:25:31,430
I'll apply for a special

600
00:25:31,460 --> 00:25:33,110
cultural grant for you.

601
00:25:33,910 --> 00:25:34,960
Ms. Gu.

602
00:25:35,080 --> 00:25:36,640
No masterpiece

603
00:25:36,660 --> 00:25:38,420
was written for money!

604
00:25:38,460 --> 00:25:39,610
Mr. Shao.

605
00:25:39,640 --> 00:25:41,450
You're a man of noble character.

606
00:25:41,480 --> 00:25:42,240
I admire you.

607
00:25:42,610 --> 00:25:43,460
But

608
00:25:43,590 --> 00:25:45,620
if you take my book

609
00:25:45,650 --> 00:25:47,950
as a cultural project,

610
00:25:48,720 --> 00:25:50,770
it'll be very necessary

611
00:25:50,800 --> 00:25:52,480
to apply for a grant for it.

612
00:25:54,310 --> 00:25:56,710
If you say so…

613
00:25:57,120 --> 00:25:58,140
I understand.

614
00:25:58,320 --> 00:25:59,280
I understand.

615
00:25:59,310 --> 00:26:00,190
Grandpa,

616
00:26:00,210 --> 00:26:01,170
tell us a story.

617
00:26:01,200 --> 00:26:02,930
Sure. What story should I tell?

618
00:26:03,940 --> 00:26:05,110
The story behind this monument.

619
00:26:05,110 --> 00:26:06,270
This monument

620
00:26:06,300 --> 00:26:07,420
is quite old.

621
00:26:07,450 --> 00:26:08,750
I'll tell you what the inscription

622
00:26:08,750 --> 00:26:10,090
means later.

623
00:26:10,720 --> 00:26:11,750
As for who erected it,

624
00:26:11,750 --> 00:26:13,150
you all know his name.

625
00:26:13,500 --> 00:26:15,060
Do you know Prime Minister Liu Luoguo?

626
00:26:15,060 --> 00:26:15,790
Yes.

627
00:26:16,430 --> 00:26:18,180
Back then, Flower Street

628
00:26:18,220 --> 00:26:21,190
was very famous along the canal.

629
00:26:21,380 --> 00:26:23,470
Ships coming and going all had to

630
00:26:23,470 --> 00:26:26,530
pass through the lock here and fill out official forms.

631
00:26:26,910 --> 00:26:28,090
Liu Yong

632
00:26:28,120 --> 00:26:30,520
erected this monument to thank the people

633
00:26:30,540 --> 00:26:31,960
of Flower Street,

634
00:26:32,140 --> 00:26:34,740
wishing for the Qing dynasty's

635
00:26:34,760 --> 00:26:36,290
long-lasting prosperity.

636
00:26:36,330 --> 00:26:38,640
But didn't the Qing dynasty end long ago?

637
00:26:38,670 --> 00:26:39,370
Yes.

638
00:26:39,520 --> 00:26:42,350
Do you know how the Qing dynasty ended?

639
00:26:42,370 --> 00:26:43,970
The Eight-Nation Alliance.

640
00:26:44,290 --> 00:26:45,130
Nonsense!

641
00:26:45,270 --> 00:26:46,800
They only invaded Beijing.

642
00:26:46,950 --> 00:26:48,540
Empress Dowager Cixi fled,

643
00:26:48,660 --> 00:26:50,190
but the empire didn't fall.

644
00:26:51,590 --> 00:26:52,730
Back then,

645
00:26:52,830 --> 00:26:54,890
the troops of the Alliance came here.

646
00:26:55,690 --> 00:26:57,030
There was a foreigner

647
00:26:57,210 --> 00:26:58,400
from Italy

648
00:26:59,180 --> 00:27:01,890
whose name was something

649
00:27:02,350 --> 00:27:04,490
sounding like Little Polo.

650
00:27:04,510 --> 00:27:06,260
According to the county annals,

651
00:27:06,260 --> 00:27:08,480
he came to China from the South Sea

652
00:27:08,590 --> 00:27:11,240
and rented a big ship in Hangzhou.

653
00:27:11,390 --> 00:27:13,150
He hired several servants

654
00:27:13,190 --> 00:27:14,870
and went all the way north.

655
00:27:14,890 --> 00:27:15,710
Siyi.

656
00:27:16,260 --> 00:27:17,550
Was he your ancestor?

657
00:27:17,580 --> 00:27:18,900
No, Grandma said

658
00:27:18,930 --> 00:27:21,770
my ancestors went south from the north.

659
00:27:21,780 --> 00:27:22,690
That guy went north.

660
00:27:22,690 --> 00:27:24,360
The locals

661
00:27:24,380 --> 00:27:26,570
said he carried a soul absorber with him

662
00:27:26,570 --> 00:27:28,960
and took people's souls.

663
00:27:29,080 --> 00:27:30,520
Really?

664
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:32,980
It was just a camera.

665
00:27:36,380 --> 00:27:37,470
Here, eat it.

666
00:27:37,470 --> 00:27:38,710
Siyi, it's really sweet.

667
00:27:38,710 --> 00:27:39,390
I don't want it.

668
00:27:39,390 --> 00:27:39,990
Take a bite.

669
00:27:39,990 --> 00:27:40,710
I don't want it!

670
00:27:40,710 --> 00:27:41,710
Just a bite.

671
00:27:41,710 --> 00:27:42,470
I don't eat ice cream.

672
00:27:42,470 --> 00:27:43,190
Try it.

673
00:27:43,230 --> 00:27:44,270
Don't touch me!

674
00:27:44,430 --> 00:27:45,660
Liang!

675
00:27:45,690 --> 00:27:46,590
Eat it.

676
00:27:49,030 --> 00:27:50,490
What are you doing?

677
00:27:50,520 --> 00:27:51,750
Did I hit you?

678
00:27:52,510 --> 00:27:53,980
Liang, stop it!

679
00:27:54,020 --> 00:27:54,710
Liang!

680
00:27:57,350 --> 00:27:58,320
Beat you up!

681
00:27:58,400 --> 00:27:59,230
Beat them!

682
00:27:59,230 --> 00:28:00,190
Stop!

683
00:28:03,870 --> 00:28:06,790
Stop fighting! Stop it!

684
00:28:07,730 --> 00:28:09,410
Let go! Break it up!

685
00:28:09,470 --> 00:28:10,530
What are you doing?

686
00:28:11,910 --> 00:28:12,480
Break it up!

687
00:28:12,480 --> 00:28:13,630
Get up. Let go!

688
00:28:13,650 --> 00:28:14,050
Let go!

689
00:28:14,060 --> 00:28:14,760
Let go!

690
00:28:47,820 --> 00:28:49,850
Kids, what happened to you?

691
00:28:51,110 --> 00:28:51,980
Did you…

692
00:28:52,060 --> 00:28:53,390
Did you get into a fight?

693
00:28:53,960 --> 00:28:55,230
-No!
-No!

694
00:28:55,230 --> 00:28:55,970
Nothing happened.

695
00:28:55,970 --> 00:28:57,060
Don't deny it!

696
00:28:57,320 --> 00:28:59,100
Look at you.

697
00:29:00,030 --> 00:29:01,030
What happened?

698
00:29:01,230 --> 00:29:02,140
It was…

699
00:29:02,170 --> 00:29:04,580
It was self-defense.

700
00:29:04,610 --> 00:29:05,920
Shao Xingchi!

701
00:29:07,660 --> 00:29:08,660
Come home with me!

702
00:29:11,510 --> 00:29:13,170
Wanghe, let's go.

703
00:29:13,810 --> 00:29:15,050
Mom, wait.

704
00:29:15,260 --> 00:29:15,720
Mom...

705
00:29:15,770 --> 00:29:16,880
Mom, it's not like that.

706
00:29:16,880 --> 00:29:18,200
Mom, listen…

707
00:29:18,400 --> 00:29:19,750
H-Hold on.

708
00:29:19,780 --> 00:29:20,990
What's wrong with you?

709
00:29:20,990 --> 00:29:22,220
Let me walk you home.

710
00:29:22,360 --> 00:29:23,100
Come in.

711
00:29:23,100 --> 00:29:24,630
Mom, I didn't start it!

712
00:29:24,630 --> 00:29:26,150
They started it.

713
00:29:26,280 --> 00:29:26,720
Mom.

714
00:29:26,750 --> 00:29:27,710
Can't you stay out of trouble

715
00:29:27,710 --> 00:29:28,910
for just one day?

716
00:29:28,950 --> 00:29:29,470
Let's go take a look.

717
00:29:29,470 --> 00:29:30,470
You taught me to be righteous!

718
00:29:30,470 --> 00:29:31,790
Righteous?

719
00:29:31,790 --> 00:29:32,720
Go ahead. Hit me!

720
00:29:32,740 --> 00:29:34,570
Hit me all you want.

721
00:29:34,590 --> 00:29:37,220
What? You feel aggrieved?

722
00:29:37,550 --> 00:29:38,190
You wanna hit me again?

723
00:29:38,190 --> 00:29:39,910
Go ahead!

724
00:29:41,730 --> 00:29:42,410
Fine.

725
00:29:42,440 --> 00:29:43,810
Fine. I won't hit you.

726
00:29:43,830 --> 00:29:44,550
Tell me

727
00:29:44,550 --> 00:29:45,310
what happened.

728
00:29:45,310 --> 00:29:46,110
Who did you fight with?

729
00:29:46,110 --> 00:29:48,510
Siyi was bullied

730
00:29:48,510 --> 00:29:49,990
by a bunch of punks at school.

731
00:29:49,990 --> 00:29:52,030
How could I just stand by?

732
00:29:57,750 --> 00:29:58,560
Sorry,

733
00:29:59,340 --> 00:30:00,370
I was wrong.

734
00:30:02,110 --> 00:30:03,190
Alright?

735
00:30:06,610 --> 00:30:07,910
But no matter what,

736
00:30:07,950 --> 00:30:08,750
in the future,

737
00:30:09,220 --> 00:30:10,570
don't fight again.

738
00:30:10,760 --> 00:30:11,510
Understand?

739
00:30:14,230 --> 00:30:15,280
Also,

740
00:30:16,180 --> 00:30:17,520
Siyi

741
00:30:17,950 --> 00:30:19,150
is sensitive.

742
00:30:19,410 --> 00:30:21,450
She's not as strong as you guys.

743
00:30:21,470 --> 00:30:23,990
Help her more.

744
00:30:24,020 --> 00:30:25,890
Treat her like your sister.

745
00:30:25,910 --> 00:30:26,900
Look out for her.

746
00:30:28,010 --> 00:30:28,940
Got it?

747
00:30:30,060 --> 00:30:30,740
Yes.

748
00:30:31,800 --> 00:30:32,650
Siyi,

749
00:30:32,920 --> 00:30:34,920
you're Wanghe's sister from now on.

750
00:30:38,860 --> 00:30:40,170
Are you hurt?

751
00:30:40,640 --> 00:30:41,470
No.

752
00:30:43,500 --> 00:30:44,420
Grandma,

753
00:30:44,800 --> 00:30:47,560
how long have our neighbors been living here?

754
00:30:51,320 --> 00:30:53,720
Very, very long.

755
00:30:56,180 --> 00:30:58,850
The Zhou family in the front yard

756
00:30:59,020 --> 00:31:01,600
moved here right after this place was built.

757
00:31:02,040 --> 00:31:04,620
I was there when Haikuo was born.

758
00:31:05,230 --> 00:31:07,200
He was such a sweet baby.

759
00:31:07,200 --> 00:31:09,130
He barely cried or threw tantrums.

760
00:31:09,150 --> 00:31:10,390
He was also smart.

761
00:31:10,530 --> 00:31:11,840
Before all his baby teeth came in,

762
00:31:11,840 --> 00:31:13,840
he could already recite many poems.

763
00:31:14,440 --> 00:31:16,470
♫When the moon shines in the sky♫

764
00:31:14,750 --> 00:31:15,720
Grandpa Zhou

765
00:31:15,750 --> 00:31:17,350
is an educated man.

766
00:31:17,080 --> 00:31:18,920
♫And it's cooling in the yard♫

767
00:31:17,510 --> 00:31:19,670
The children raised by educated people

768
00:31:19,380 --> 00:31:22,850
♫Who is still by your side?♫

769
00:31:19,670 --> 00:31:21,030
are different.

770
00:31:23,840 --> 00:31:27,450
♫As time passes♫

771
00:31:24,030 --> 00:31:25,990
The Shao family next door…

772
00:31:28,230 --> 00:31:29,750
It's been eight years, I think.

773
00:31:28,260 --> 00:31:31,710
♫Is a lifetime really that long?♫

774
00:31:30,300 --> 00:31:33,430
When they came, Xingchi was only two and a half years old.

775
00:31:33,770 --> 00:31:36,050
He was always hungry.

776
00:31:35,670 --> 00:31:37,310
♫When youthful company fades♫

777
00:31:36,070 --> 00:31:37,600
He cried when he was hungry,

778
00:31:37,620 --> 00:31:39,700
and it was impossible to shush him.

779
00:31:37,870 --> 00:31:39,790
♫Leaving only small talk and pleasantries♫

780
00:31:40,490 --> 00:31:43,960
♫Spring feels short, while autumn lingers♫

781
00:31:40,900 --> 00:31:42,320
What about Wanghe?

782
00:31:42,340 --> 00:31:43,110
His family

783
00:31:43,150 --> 00:31:45,470
moved here with Fenghua's family.

784
00:31:45,290 --> 00:31:48,790
♫A gentle breeze carries dreams away♫

785
00:31:45,800 --> 00:31:47,600
They're all kind

786
00:31:47,880 --> 00:31:49,290
and very righteous.

787
00:31:49,600 --> 00:31:53,720
♫Dreamland and dreams♫

788
00:31:50,560 --> 00:31:51,590
Back then,

789
00:31:52,180 --> 00:31:54,100
when your dad was sick,

790
00:31:54,930 --> 00:31:58,060
I went to the provincial capital for treatment with him.

791
00:31:58,440 --> 00:32:01,660
♫Life is long♫

792
00:31:59,860 --> 00:32:02,490
I didn't know anyone there.

793
00:32:02,700 --> 00:32:06,550
Your Uncle Xie helped us a lot

794
00:32:02,940 --> 00:32:05,960
♫No need to dwell♫

795
00:32:06,550 --> 00:32:09,430
and was always there for us.

796
00:32:07,110 --> 00:32:10,480
♫Like moonlight♫

797
00:32:09,430 --> 00:32:11,540
He lost over 10 kilograms.

798
00:32:11,830 --> 00:32:15,190
♫Don't forget♫

799
00:32:14,200 --> 00:32:16,150
They're all good people.

800
00:32:17,260 --> 00:32:20,190
♫Life is long♫

801
00:32:17,940 --> 00:32:20,580
My mom's neighbors were like strangers.

802
00:32:20,600 --> 00:32:22,190
They didn't even say hi when they met.

803
00:32:21,310 --> 00:32:24,740
♫No need to dwell♫

804
00:32:25,190 --> 00:32:27,470
As the old saying goes,

805
00:32:25,880 --> 00:32:29,090
♫Like moonlight♫

806
00:32:27,470 --> 00:32:29,720
good neighbors are more helpful than distant relatives.

807
00:32:29,720 --> 00:32:33,250
But it's rare for neighbors to see each other as family.

808
00:32:30,500 --> 00:32:35,220
♫The old times♫

809
00:32:34,830 --> 00:32:36,550
You should cherish them.

810
00:32:37,480 --> 00:32:38,520
I will.

811
00:32:40,140 --> 00:32:41,860
Good girl.

812
00:32:41,870 --> 00:32:43,960
All right. Do your homework.

813
00:32:55,460 --> 00:32:57,230
♫When the moon shines in the sky♫

814
00:32:58,120 --> 00:32:59,650
♫And it's cooling in the yard♫

815
00:33:00,300 --> 00:33:03,750
♫Who is still by your side?♫

816
00:33:05,030 --> 00:33:08,450
♫As time passes♫

817
00:33:09,340 --> 00:33:12,810
♫Is a lifetime really that long?♫

818
00:33:23,580 --> 00:33:25,320
Mr. Zhou, let me tell you.

819
00:33:26,100 --> 00:33:27,830
The new ship

820
00:33:27,830 --> 00:33:29,490
is a good bargain.

821
00:33:29,520 --> 00:33:30,870
You know why? Because

822
00:33:30,870 --> 00:33:33,430
the main engine of this ship

823
00:33:34,060 --> 00:33:35,350
is imported.

824
00:33:35,740 --> 00:33:37,510
A foreign engine.

825
00:33:37,510 --> 00:33:39,270
It's fuel-efficient

826
00:33:39,270 --> 00:33:40,680
and makes less noise.

827
00:33:40,680 --> 00:33:41,410
Hey.

828
00:33:41,870 --> 00:33:42,630
Have a seat.

829
00:33:42,630 --> 00:33:43,230
Hello.

830
00:33:43,230 --> 00:33:43,670
Hello.

831
00:33:43,670 --> 00:33:44,660
We're talking about the engine,

832
00:33:44,660 --> 00:33:45,660
the latest model.

833
00:33:46,980 --> 00:33:48,690
We've found a buyer

834
00:33:48,720 --> 00:33:50,230
for our old ship.

835
00:33:50,550 --> 00:33:51,910
He offered a fair price.

836
00:33:51,910 --> 00:33:53,020
Right, Lao'er?

837
00:33:53,220 --> 00:33:54,150
As for the new ship,

838
00:33:54,150 --> 00:33:56,060
we've contacted

839
00:33:56,060 --> 00:33:57,440
the shipyard.

840
00:33:57,910 --> 00:33:59,430
As long as the payment is made,

841
00:33:59,430 --> 00:34:01,390
we can get the ship in one week.

842
00:34:01,590 --> 00:34:02,590
So fast.

843
00:34:02,910 --> 00:34:03,830
So, I've explained

844
00:34:03,830 --> 00:34:05,190
everything to you.

845
00:34:05,190 --> 00:34:06,870
If you think it's feasible,

846
00:34:06,890 --> 00:34:08,040
chip in.

847
00:34:08,080 --> 00:34:09,580
If you're not interested,

848
00:34:09,620 --> 00:34:10,949
drop out.

849
00:34:11,020 --> 00:34:12,980
We'll still be friends either way.

850
00:34:12,980 --> 00:34:14,300
Don't feel pressured.

851
00:34:14,350 --> 00:34:15,590
No pressure.

852
00:34:15,590 --> 00:34:16,389
I told you.

853
00:34:16,389 --> 00:34:17,870
We'll chip in, right?

854
00:34:17,909 --> 00:34:19,350
Dad, I've brought the money.

855
00:34:19,350 --> 00:34:20,870
Cut me in.

856
00:34:21,389 --> 00:34:22,580
No, no, no.

857
00:34:22,630 --> 00:34:23,389
Granny Ma.

858
00:34:23,520 --> 00:34:24,179
Don't do this.

859
00:34:24,179 --> 00:34:25,969
You don't have much money,

860
00:34:26,070 --> 00:34:28,219
and now you have a granddaughter to raise.

861
00:34:28,219 --> 00:34:29,560
You don't have to invest,

862
00:34:29,560 --> 00:34:31,800
but you can keep your shares.

863
00:34:31,840 --> 00:34:32,610
Exactly.

864
00:34:32,830 --> 00:34:33,750
No way.

865
00:34:33,750 --> 00:34:35,469
I'd feel terrible.

866
00:34:35,469 --> 00:34:36,550
No, no!

867
00:34:36,590 --> 00:34:38,000
What's wrong with you?

868
00:34:38,469 --> 00:34:39,790
Tiancheng, listen.

869
00:34:39,830 --> 00:34:41,190
Don't feel pressured.

870
00:34:41,429 --> 00:34:42,510
We all made money

871
00:34:42,550 --> 00:34:44,659
from your ship in the past.

872
00:34:45,310 --> 00:34:46,389
Whether this is profitable or not,

873
00:34:46,389 --> 00:34:47,670
with the canal still operating,

874
00:34:47,670 --> 00:34:50,150
I don't believe you, Boss Xie,

875
00:34:50,150 --> 00:34:51,550
can't make ends meet.

876
00:34:52,389 --> 00:34:53,110
Yeah!

877
00:34:53,139 --> 00:34:53,960
Yeah!

878
00:34:53,960 --> 00:34:54,310
Okay.

879
00:34:54,350 --> 00:34:55,880
We'll keep your money.

880
00:34:56,190 --> 00:34:57,510
No need to ask us.

881
00:34:57,550 --> 00:34:58,830
We all listen to you.

882
00:34:58,830 --> 00:35:00,150
This is our money.

883
00:35:00,150 --> 00:35:01,590
We're also in.

884
00:35:01,630 --> 00:35:02,150
Look.

885
00:35:02,150 --> 00:35:02,820
Yes.

886
00:35:02,910 --> 00:35:03,990
Here's the money.

887
00:35:05,180 --> 00:35:06,740
Is the money enough?

888
00:35:06,950 --> 00:35:09,230
I think it's almost enough.

889
00:35:09,270 --> 00:35:11,070
Later, Lao'er and I

890
00:35:11,670 --> 00:35:12,750
will count…

891
00:35:12,750 --> 00:35:13,350
Count the money.

892
00:35:13,350 --> 00:35:14,830
Count the money, and then decide

893
00:35:14,830 --> 00:35:16,980
how many shares you get based on the amount of your money.

894
00:35:16,980 --> 00:35:18,670
We'll do it the old way.

895
00:35:18,670 --> 00:35:18,990
Okay.

896
00:35:18,990 --> 00:35:19,480
Are we clear?

897
00:35:19,480 --> 00:35:19,990
Yeah.

898
00:35:19,990 --> 00:35:21,830
Don't worry. After we make the payment,

899
00:35:21,830 --> 00:35:22,950
we can see

900
00:35:22,950 --> 00:35:24,070
our new ship

901
00:35:24,110 --> 00:35:25,910
in one week!

902
00:35:46,670 --> 00:35:47,670
Let me have a look.

903
00:35:47,670 --> 00:35:49,030
I'm not done yet.

904
00:35:49,030 --> 00:35:50,150
Let me take a look.

905
00:35:50,150 --> 00:35:51,030
Give it to her.

906
00:35:51,030 --> 00:35:51,950
You bad boy.

907
00:35:57,550 --> 00:35:58,580
Can I have a try?

908
00:35:58,760 --> 00:35:59,960
You want to have a try?

909
00:35:59,980 --> 00:36:00,780
Okay.

910
00:36:03,550 --> 00:36:05,710
Son, after a few years,

911
00:36:05,710 --> 00:36:07,430
when the Grand Canal is dredged,

912
00:36:07,430 --> 00:36:08,950
we'll sail this ship

913
00:36:08,950 --> 00:36:11,060
all the way north to Beijing!

914
00:36:11,060 --> 00:36:11,630
I want to go too!

915
00:36:11,630 --> 00:36:12,580
No problem.

916
00:36:12,670 --> 00:36:13,150
Alright.

917
00:36:13,150 --> 00:36:14,080
Let me take over.

918
00:36:17,110 --> 00:36:18,030
Dad.

919
00:36:18,030 --> 00:36:19,550
I've never seen the sea.

920
00:36:19,550 --> 00:36:20,950
When can we sail this ship

921
00:36:20,950 --> 00:36:22,080
to the sea?

922
00:36:22,080 --> 00:36:23,500
Sail this ship to the sea?

923
00:36:23,500 --> 00:36:23,960
Yes.

924
00:36:23,960 --> 00:36:25,700
It may look big,

925
00:36:25,700 --> 00:36:26,580
but on the sea,

926
00:36:26,630 --> 00:36:28,270
it's just a small ship.

927
00:36:28,270 --> 00:36:30,150
To withstand the winds and waves on the sea,

928
00:36:30,150 --> 00:36:32,570
we need a much bigger ship.

929
00:36:32,710 --> 00:36:34,630
You know what a 10,000-ton ship is like?

930
00:36:34,630 --> 00:36:35,430
After I grow up,

931
00:36:35,430 --> 00:36:36,630
I'll buy you a 10,000-ton ship,

932
00:36:36,630 --> 00:36:38,160
and we'll sail it to the sea.

933
00:36:39,670 --> 00:36:41,270
Good boy. You've got ambition!

934
00:36:41,270 --> 00:36:42,790
I'll wait for that day.

935
00:36:44,320 --> 00:36:45,520
You've got ambition.

936
00:36:45,940 --> 00:36:47,200
A 10,000-ton ship.

937
00:37:06,400 --> 00:37:09,030
Grandma, I'm taking Siyi for a swim.

938
00:37:09,100 --> 00:37:10,280
Grandma, can I go with them

939
00:37:10,280 --> 00:37:11,110
for a swim?

940
00:37:11,110 --> 00:37:11,910
Be careful.

941
00:37:11,910 --> 00:37:12,450
Okay.

942
00:37:12,490 --> 00:37:13,010
Okay.

943
00:37:13,230 --> 00:37:14,190
Wanghe.

944
00:37:14,190 --> 00:37:14,630
We're leaving!

945
00:37:14,630 --> 00:37:15,510
Take care of your friends!

946
00:37:15,510 --> 00:37:17,030
Fenghua, keep an eye on Siyi.

947
00:37:17,030 --> 00:37:19,160
Don't swim too far into the deep water.

948
00:37:20,290 --> 00:37:22,430
Fenghua, you're as slow as a turtle!

949
00:37:22,730 --> 00:37:23,570
Hurry up!

950
00:37:31,180 --> 00:37:33,140
I want to be a captain in the future.

951
00:37:33,170 --> 00:37:34,180
I'll buy a big ship

952
00:37:34,390 --> 00:37:35,270
and sail all the way south.

953
00:37:35,270 --> 00:37:37,180
I'll go to Sanjiangkou, then out to the open sea,

954
00:37:37,180 --> 00:37:39,000
and onward to the Suez Canal.

955
00:37:39,330 --> 00:37:40,280
I'll go with you.

956
00:37:40,780 --> 00:37:41,690
No women on board.

957
00:37:41,690 --> 00:37:44,220
I'll buy a ship myself and be a female captain.

958
00:37:46,590 --> 00:37:48,190
Can you even swim?

959
00:37:48,210 --> 00:37:49,730
I swim better than you.

960
00:37:49,770 --> 00:37:50,690
Stop bragging.

961
00:37:52,230 --> 00:37:53,890
Let's find it out in the water.

962
00:37:54,220 --> 00:37:55,180
No problem.

963
00:37:56,070 --> 00:37:57,830
The one who gets there first wins.

964
00:37:57,830 --> 00:37:58,710
Okay.

965
00:37:58,730 --> 00:37:59,800
-Come on.
-Come on.

966
00:38:08,070 --> 00:38:09,080
Ready?

967
00:38:11,450 --> 00:38:13,560
One, two, three, jump!

968
00:38:31,550 --> 00:38:32,350
Slow down!

969
00:39:55,780 --> 00:39:58,020
[2007]

970
00:40:11,390 --> 00:40:12,120
Fenghua!

971
00:40:12,170 --> 00:40:13,140
Jump in!

972
00:40:13,430 --> 00:40:14,310
Jump in!

973
00:40:14,310 --> 00:40:15,000
Jump in!

974
00:40:15,000 --> 00:40:16,190
Jump in!

975
00:40:16,190 --> 00:40:18,350
I told you my mom washed my swimsuit.

976
00:40:18,350 --> 00:40:19,440
So what?

977
00:40:19,470 --> 00:40:20,070
Just jump in.

978
00:40:20,070 --> 00:40:20,780
Jump in!

979
00:40:20,800 --> 00:40:21,600
Jump in!

980
00:40:21,600 --> 00:40:22,230
Jump in!

981
00:40:22,230 --> 00:40:23,870
Siyi, how can you side with them?

982
00:40:23,870 --> 00:40:25,710
Jump in. Come on!

983
00:40:25,790 --> 00:40:26,390
Come on.

984
00:40:26,420 --> 00:40:27,190
Jump in!

985
00:40:27,190 --> 00:40:28,270
-Jump in!
-Come on!

986
00:40:28,270 --> 00:40:29,150
I'm warning you.

987
00:40:29,150 --> 00:40:29,830
Stop splashing,

988
00:40:29,830 --> 00:40:31,560
or you'll have to go home naked.

989
00:40:32,070 --> 00:40:32,960
Jump in!

990
00:40:33,070 --> 00:40:33,950
Jump in!

991
00:40:33,950 --> 00:40:35,360
Don't make me come up there and push you.

992
00:40:35,360 --> 00:40:36,550
Are you too scared to jump?

993
00:40:36,550 --> 00:40:38,010
Why would I be scared?

994
00:40:38,330 --> 00:40:39,690
You think I'm scared?

995
00:40:42,430 --> 00:40:43,510
Don't take away our clothes!

996
00:40:43,510 --> 00:40:44,870
Leave something for me!

997
00:40:44,870 --> 00:40:46,670
There's nothing I don't dare do.

998
00:40:47,350 --> 00:40:49,190
Go home naked!

999
00:40:49,370 --> 00:40:49,900
Fenghua!

1000
00:40:49,910 --> 00:40:50,390
Fenghua!

1001
00:40:50,390 --> 00:40:51,560
Xia Fenghua!

1002
00:40:54,120 --> 00:40:55,160
-Fenghua!
-Fenghua!

1003
00:40:55,160 --> 00:40:55,630
Help!

1004
00:40:55,710 --> 00:40:57,640
That's what you get for messing with me.

1005
00:40:57,640 --> 00:40:58,860
Help!

1006
00:40:58,900 --> 00:41:00,550
Someone fell into the river!

1007
00:41:00,570 --> 00:41:01,160
Let's go.

1008
00:41:02,620 --> 00:41:04,310
You can't die!

1009
00:41:04,330 --> 00:41:06,840
We're in so much debt!

1010
00:41:07,070 --> 00:41:09,910
How are our kid and I going to live?

1011
00:41:09,940 --> 00:41:11,410
Watch your step!

1012
00:41:32,630 --> 00:41:33,630
What happened?

1013
00:41:33,670 --> 00:41:34,550
Mom.

1014
00:41:35,670 --> 00:41:36,840
What's going on?

1015
00:41:37,450 --> 00:41:38,790
Wu, the seafarer,

1016
00:41:40,350 --> 00:41:41,720
couldn't pay his debt

1017
00:41:41,740 --> 00:41:43,090
and took his own life.

1018
00:41:43,130 --> 00:41:44,830
Didn't he just buy a new ship?

1019
00:41:44,900 --> 00:41:46,300
How is he in debt?

1020
00:41:46,630 --> 00:41:47,310
He gambled?

1021
00:41:47,310 --> 00:41:49,520
He borrowed money to buy the ship, but it was hard to get orders.

1022
00:41:49,520 --> 00:41:51,310
He shipped coal last month

1023
00:41:51,340 --> 00:41:52,400
and counted on it to pay his debt.

1024
00:41:52,400 --> 00:41:53,600
But he overloaded the ship

1025
00:41:53,600 --> 00:41:55,150
and was fined a lot of money.

1026
00:41:55,720 --> 00:41:57,440
There are more and more highways

1027
00:41:57,440 --> 00:41:59,170
and fewer and fewer ships.

1028
00:41:59,390 --> 00:42:00,490
What should we do?

1029
00:42:00,720 --> 00:42:02,170
The tide of change

1030
00:42:02,590 --> 00:42:04,720
is unstoppable

1031
00:42:04,750 --> 00:42:08,180
and leaves its mark on everyone.

1032
00:42:08,230 --> 00:42:09,760
Seven years ago,

1033
00:42:09,780 --> 00:42:12,370
the Beijing-Shanghai Expressway, which spans the Yellow River

1034
00:42:12,370 --> 00:42:15,820
and leaps over the Yangtze River, was put into operation.

1035
00:42:15,960 --> 00:42:18,500
Since then, it has greatly promoted

1036
00:42:18,530 --> 00:42:22,530
the development of areas along the route and even the national economy.

1037
00:42:22,810 --> 00:42:26,450
The cars on shore are running faster and faster.

1038
00:42:26,620 --> 00:42:29,090
The seafarers who make a living on the water

1039
00:42:29,130 --> 00:42:31,760
find it harder and harder

1040
00:42:31,780 --> 00:42:34,240
to feel a sense of honor and accomplishment.

1041
00:42:34,700 --> 00:42:37,870
Business is getting smaller and smaller.

1042
00:42:37,900 --> 00:42:40,540
Profits are dwindling.

1043
00:42:41,350 --> 00:42:42,850
The shipping business on the canal

1044
00:42:42,850 --> 00:42:45,270
seems to be moving forward

1045
00:42:45,310 --> 00:42:48,100
with this fast-paced world,

1046
00:42:48,220 --> 00:42:51,150
but actually, it's going in the opposite direction.

1047
00:42:51,500 --> 00:42:53,300
However, the spirit of the canal

1048
00:42:53,330 --> 00:42:57,360
is already flowing in the blood of the canal people.

1049
00:42:57,750 --> 00:42:59,750
The new era has presented new challenges

1050
00:42:59,750 --> 00:43:01,740
for the young generation

1051
00:43:01,770 --> 00:43:03,700
living by the canal.

